President Donald Trump has announced his intention to nominate Robert Williams as the Assistant Secretary of State for South Asian Affairs. Williams has over 20 years of experience in South Asia and Afghanistan affairs, working as an analyst and intelligence officer. He currently serves at the Defense Intelligence Agency as Associate Deputy Director for Intelligence and Directorate for Operations. Williams has also been an adjunct professor at Georgetown University's School of Foreign Service. The President also intends to nominate Charles Glazer as a Member of the United States Advisory Commission on Public Diplomacy for the remainder of a three-year term.